Package: pdn-net
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Tom Fanning <tom@m0lte.uk>
Depends: libc6, libgcc-s1, libstdc++6
Recommends: packetnet, iproute2
Section: net
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/packet-net/pdn-net
Description: IP-over-packet-radio TUN host stack (pdn-net)
 Brings up a pdn0 TUN interface and bridges IP packets to and from AX.25 UI
 frames (standard IP-over-AX.25, PID 0xCC) through a Packet.NET (pdn) node over
 RHPv2. Ordinary Linux IP software - ssh, mosh, mqtt, ping - runs unmodified
 over packet radio; nothing in the application knows it is talking over radio.
 .
 Self-contained: bundles its own .NET runtime, so no system .NET is required.
 The systemd unit ships DISABLED - configure /etc/pdn-net/pdn-net.json and
 assign the pdn0 interface an address, then `systemctl enable --now pdn-net`.
